Files / Code Written:

HaloDensityEvolution.py

Prepared code to compute radial density profiles for MW+M31 snapshots from 100 to 800.

Uses a shell-based method to calculate densities in logarithmic radial bins.

Includes progress printing to track snapshot processing.

Intended output: heatmap of density evolution (plotting code included but not executed).

HaloDensityProfile.py

Prepared code to calculate the density profile for a single snapshot (445).

Comparison with analytic profiles: Hernquist, NFW, and Isothermal.

Plotting code included but plots not generated yet.

HaloDifferentialDensity.py

Prepared code to compute differential density profile using the enclosed mass method for snapshot 445.

Includes calculation of cumulative mass, radial differences, and corresponding density.

Plotting code included but plots not generated yet.

